# API Rules

Read and follow ALL rules in `.ai-suite/phases/05-api-design.md` and `.ai-suite/phases/07-backend.md`.

Key non-negotiable rules:
- **Negative Testing Focus**: New API endpoints must include negative tests to verify error handling.
- Enforce strict input validation at the API boundary before any processing.
- Never expose internal system details, stack traces, or raw database structures in API responses.
- Follow strict REST naming conventions (resource-based URLs, plural nouns).
- Include comprehensive docstrings/JSDoc and OpenAPI (Swagger) representations where applicable.
